Discover SDP data by downloading catalog information.

Source: R/sdp_catalog_functions.R
sdp_get_catalog.Rd

Discover SDP data by downloading catalog information.

Usage

sdp_get_catalog(
  domains = c("UG", "UER", "GT"),
  types = c("Mask", "Topo", "Vegetation", "Hydro", "Planning", "Radiation", "Snow",
    "Climate", "Imagery", "Supplemental"),
  releases = c("Basemaps", "Release1", "Release2", "Release3", "Release4"),
  timeseries_types = c("Single", "Yearly", "Seasonal", "Monthly", "Daily"),
  deprecated = FALSE,
  return_stac = FALSE
)

Arguments

domains

The spatial domain of the desired data product.

types

The type of product to return.

releases

Which release (group) of data products to return.

timeseries_types

Some datasets are structured as single datasets (e.g. Single), and others are time-series with various periods (e.g.Monthly).

deprecated

Should older versions of datasets be returned, or just the latest version?

return_stac

NOT IMPLEMENTED: Should the results be returned as a Spatio-temporal Asset Catalog? Otherwise return and ordinary data frame.

Value

A data frame containing basic catalog information for the matched data products.

Examples


## Gets information on all current datasets.
sdp_cat <- sdp_get_catalog()
str(sdp_cat)

## Gets a subset of catalog entries for the Upper Gunnison (UG) domain.
sdp_sub <- sdp_get_catalog(domains="UG", types="Vegetation",
                          deprecated=FALSE,return_stac=FALSE)
